{"data":{"certs":{"edges":[{"node":{"frontmatter":{"date":"2021-12-18","title":"8th Workshop on Collaborative Scientific Software Development and Management of Open Source Scientific Packages","organizer":"The Abdus Salam International Centre for Theoretical Physics","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/png;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/mobile/static/10551e0ad6be37c4466d66bb65219573/b7af2/ictp.png","srcSet":"/mobile/static/10551e0ad6be37c4466d66bb65219573/559e2/ictp.png 58w,\n/mobile/static/10551e0ad6be37c4466d66bb65219573/10479/ictp.png 115w,\n/mobile/static/10551e0ad6be37c4466d66bb65219573/b7af2/ictp.png 230w,\n/mobile/static/10551e0ad6be37c4466d66bb65219573/24f3d/ictp.png 460w","sizes":"(min-width: 230px) 230px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/mobile/static/10551e0ad6be37c4466d66bb65219573/b423f/ictp.avif 58w,\n/mobile/static/10551e0ad6be37c4466d66bb65219573/4b692/ictp.avif 115w,\n/mobile/static/10551e0ad6be37c4466d66bb65219573/f6006/ictp.avif 230w,\n/mobile/static/10551e0ad6be37c4466d66bb65219573/16325/ictp.avif 460w","type":"image/avif","sizes":"(min-width: 230px) 230px, 100vw"},{"srcSet":"/mobile/static/10551e0ad6be37c4466d66bb65219573/5aa2f/ictp.webp 58w,\n/mobile/static/10551e0ad6be37c4466d66bb65219573/f8466/ictp.webp 115w,\n/mobile/static/10551e0ad6be37c4466d66bb65219573/84992/ictp.webp 230w,\n/mobile/static/10551e0ad6be37c4466d66bb65219573/b5c5b/ictp.webp 460w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min-width: 230px) 230px, 100vw"}]},"width":230,"height":230}}},"external":"https://indico.ictp.it/event/9700/overview","topics":["Effective collaborative development with multiple co-authors","Python / shell scripts as glue code","Modular, reusable software design","Software optimization","Version control and release cycles","Automated testing frameworks","Structured documentation","Management of open source scientific packages","Continuous integration & deployment","Conversational development"],"skills":["DevOp Practices","Git","GitLab","CI/CD"]},"html":"<p>Writing software has become central to research in many fields of science. This school aims to give early-career scientists an introduction to a variety of topics that help them to write efficient, clean, maintainable and long-lived code that is useful beyond solving an immediate problem. In a mixture of talks and many hands-on sessions, the focus lies on showing best practices and building fundamental skills in creating, extending and collaborating on modular and reusable software.</p>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"date":"2021-12-06","title":"Applied Data Science II: Machine Learning & Statistical Analysis (with honors)","organizer":"WorldQuant University","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/png;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/mobile/static/3413b07a137df2bd460c740a0491f645/b7af2/applied_data_science2.png","srcSet":"/mobile/static/3413b07a137df2bd460c740a0491f645/559e2/applied_data_science2.png 58w,\n/mobile/static/3413b07a137df2bd460c740a0491f645/10479/applied_data_science2.png 115w,\n/mobile/static/3413b07a137df2bd460c740a0491f645/b7af2/applied_data_science2.png 230w,\n/mobile/static/3413b07a137df2bd460c740a0491f645/24f3d/applied_data_science2.png 460w","sizes":"(min-width: 230px) 230px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/mobile/static/3413b07a137df2bd460c740a0491f645/b423f/applied_data_science2.avif 58w,\n/mobile/static/3413b07a137df2bd460c740a0491f645/4b692/applied_data_science2.avif 115w,\n/mobile/static/3413b07a137df2bd460c740a0491f645/f6006/applied_data_science2.avif 230w,\n/mobile/static/3413b07a137df2bd460c740a0491f645/16325/applied_data_science2.avif 460w","type":"image/avif","sizes":"(min-width: 230px) 230px, 100vw"},{"srcSet":"/mobile/static/3413b07a137df2bd460c740a0491f645/5aa2f/applied_data_science2.webp 58w,\n/mobile/static/3413b07a137df2bd460c740a0491f645/f8466/applied_data_science2.webp 115w,\n/mobile/static/3413b07a137df2bd460c740a0491f645/84992/applied_data_science2.webp 230w,\n/mobile/static/3413b07a137df2bd460c740a0491f645/b5c5b/applied_data_science2.webp 460w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min-width: 230px) 230px, 100vw"}]},"width":230,"height":230}}},"external":"https://www.credly.com/badges/ba9d6907-4355-44c5-8c41-1a7d7acb98e0/public_url","topics":["Anomaly Detection, Clustering","Decision Trees, Support Vector Machine, Random Forest, Gradient Boosting Trees","Dimensionality Reduction","Linear Regression, Logistic Regression","Machine Learning, Model Fitting, Model Tuning","Natural Language Processing","Supervised Learning, Unsupervised Learning","Time Series Analysis"],"skills":["Data Cleaning","Handling Missing Values","Feature Engineering","Categorical Encoding","Word Embedding"]},"html":"<p>Earners of this badge have previously earned the badge \"Applied Data Science I: Scientific Computing &#x26; Python.\" Additionally, they have successfully completed 2 mini projects and maintained a cumulative average score of 90% or above. The descriptions and skills needed to complete these projects are listed below.\nIn mini project 1, earners of this badge worked with nursing home inspection data from the United States, predicting which providers may be fined and for how much. They used the scikit-learn Python package to construct progressively more complicated machine learning models. They had to impute missing values, apply feature engineering, and encode categorical data.\nIn mini project 2, earners of this badge used natural language processing to train various machine learning models to predict an Amazon review rating based on the text of the review. Further, they used one of the trained models to gain insight on the reviews, identifying words that are highly polar. With these highly polar words identified, one can understand what words highly influence the model’s prediction.</p>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"date":"2020-09-15","title":"DeepLearning.AI TensorFlow Developer Professional Certificate","organizer":"DeepLearning.AI","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/png;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/mobile/static/1e726d170d968e103587c4f1f30bc58f/b7af2/deeplearning.png","srcSet":"/mobile/static/1e726d170d968e103587c4f1f30bc58f/559e2/deeplearning.png 58w,\n/mobile/static/1e726d170d968e103587c4f1f30bc58f/10479/deeplearning.png 115w,\n/mobile/static/1e726d170d968e103587c4f1f30bc58f/b7af2/deeplearning.png 230w,\n/mobile/static/1e726d170d968e103587c4f1f30bc58f/24f3d/deeplearning.png 460w","sizes":"(min-width: 230px) 230px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/mobile/static/1e726d170d968e103587c4f1f30bc58f/b423f/deeplearning.avif 58w,\n/mobile/static/1e726d170d968e103587c4f1f30bc58f/4b692/deeplearning.avif 115w,\n/mobile/static/1e726d170d968e103587c4f1f30bc58f/f6006/deeplearning.avif 230w,\n/mobile/static/1e726d170d968e103587c4f1f30bc58f/16325/deeplearning.avif 460w","type":"image/avif","sizes":"(min-width: 230px) 230px, 100vw"},{"srcSet":"/mobile/static/1e726d170d968e103587c4f1f30bc58f/5aa2f/deeplearning.webp 58w,\n/mobile/static/1e726d170d968e103587c4f1f30bc58f/f8466/deeplearning.webp 115w,\n/mobile/static/1e726d170d968e103587c4f1f30bc58f/84992/deeplearning.webp 230w,\n/mobile/static/1e726d170d968e103587c4f1f30bc58f/b5c5b/deeplearning.webp 460w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min-width: 230px) 230px, 100vw"}]},"width":230,"height":230}}},"external":"https://coursera.org/share/d032b77a2b7a981ca725fecda3ba76e6","topics":["Introduction to TensorFlow for Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, and Deep Learning","Convolutional Neural Networks in TensorFlow","Natural Language Processing in TensorFlow","Sequences, Time Series and Prediction"],"skills":["Computer Vision","Convolutional Neural Network","Machine Learning","Natural Language Processing","Tensorflow","Inductive Transfer","Augmentation","Dropouts","Tokenization","Recurrent Neural Network","Forecasting","Time Series"]},"html":"<p>Best practices for TensorFlow, a popular open-source machine learning framework to train a neural network for a computer vision applications.</p>\n<p>Handle real-world image data and explore strategies to prevent overfitting, including augmentation and dropout.</p>\n<p>Build natural language processing systems using TensorFlow.</p>\n<p>Apply RNNs, GRUs, and LSTMs as you train them using text repositories.</p>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"date":"2020-08-31","title":"Bayesian Methods for Machine Learning","organizer":"National Research University Higher School of Economics","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/png;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/mobile/static/6524fef7ecbdaf678c33c71b18d5450b/dd75a/hse.png","srcSet":"/mobile/static/6524fef7ecbdaf678c33c71b18d5450b/24df8/hse.png 58w,\n/mobile/static/6524fef7ecbdaf678c33c71b18d5450b/710f7/hse.png 115w,\n/mobile/static/6524fef7ecbdaf678c33c71b18d5450b/dd75a/hse.png 230w","sizes":"(min-width: 230px) 230px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/mobile/static/6524fef7ecbdaf678c33c71b18d5450b/9f9cc/hse.avif 58w,\n/mobile/static/6524fef7ecbdaf678c33c71b18d5450b/e3692/hse.avif 115w,\n/mobile/static/6524fef7ecbdaf678c33c71b18d5450b/33527/hse.avif 230w","type":"image/avif","sizes":"(min-width: 230px) 230px, 100vw"},{"srcSet":"/mobile/static/6524fef7ecbdaf678c33c71b18d5450b/c0406/hse.webp 58w,\n/mobile/static/6524fef7ecbdaf678c33c71b18d5450b/d6a25/hse.webp 115w,\n/mobile/static/6524fef7ecbdaf678c33c71b18d5450b/0aef3/hse.webp 230w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min-width: 230px) 230px, 100vw"}]},"width":230,"height":234}}},"external":"https://coursera.org/share/76c04b42341f426e70d153d783492f70","topics":["Bayesian Statistics","Probabilistic Models","Handling Missing Data","Machine Learning","Hyperparameter Tuning"],"skills":["Bayesian Optimization","Gaussian Process","Markov Chain Monte Carlo (MCMC)","Variational Bayesian Methods"]},"html":"<p>People apply Bayesian methods in many areas: from game development to drug discovery. They give superpowers to many machine learning algorithms: handling missing data, extracting much more information from small datasets. Bayesian methods also allow us to estimate uncertainty in predictions, which is a desirable feature for fields like medicine.</p>\n<p>When applied to deep learning, Bayesian methods allow you to compress your models a hundred folds, and automatically tune hyperparameters, saving your time and money.</p>\n<p>In this online HSE course we will discuss the basics of Bayesian methods: from how to define a probabilistic model to how to make predictions from it. We will see how one can automate this workflow and how to speed it up using some advanced techniques.</p>\n<p>We will also see applications of Bayesian methods to deep learning and how to generate new images with it. We will see how new drugs that cure severe diseases can be found with Bayesian methods.</p>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"date":"2020-08-16","title":"Practical Reinforcement Learning","organizer":"National Research University Higher School of Economics","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/png;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/mobile/static/6524fef7ecbdaf678c33c71b18d5450b/dd75a/hse.png","srcSet":"/mobile/static/6524fef7ecbdaf678c33c71b18d5450b/24df8/hse.png 58w,\n/mobile/static/6524fef7ecbdaf678c33c71b18d5450b/710f7/hse.png 115w,\n/mobile/static/6524fef7ecbdaf678c33c71b18d5450b/dd75a/hse.png 230w","sizes":"(min-width: 230px) 230px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/mobile/static/6524fef7ecbdaf678c33c71b18d5450b/9f9cc/hse.avif 58w,\n/mobile/static/6524fef7ecbdaf678c33c71b18d5450b/e3692/hse.avif 115w,\n/mobile/static/6524fef7ecbdaf678c33c71b18d5450b/33527/hse.avif 230w","type":"image/avif","sizes":"(min-width: 230px) 230px, 100vw"},{"srcSet":"/mobile/static/6524fef7ecbdaf678c33c71b18d5450b/c0406/hse.webp 58w,\n/mobile/static/6524fef7ecbdaf678c33c71b18d5450b/d6a25/hse.webp 115w,\n/mobile/static/6524fef7ecbdaf678c33c71b18d5450b/0aef3/hse.webp 230w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min-width: 230px) 230px, 100vw"}]},"width":230,"height":234}}},"external":"https://coursera.org/share/a200be014e0780d1673a1500e96d66da","topics":["Value/Policy Iteration","Q-Learning","Policy Gradient","Deep Neural Network for RL tasks","Hype Train","Building Game with RL"],"skills":["Reinforcement Learning Methods","Policy Building Strategy"]},"html":""}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"date":"2020-08-07","title":"Advanced Machine Learning and Signal Processing","organizer":"IBM","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/png;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/mobile/static/a5694cb204f38cef612de44d0a04aa60/b7af2/advanced_machine_signal.png","srcSet":"/mobile/static/a5694cb204f38cef612de44d0a04aa60/559e2/advanced_machine_signal.png 58w,\n/mobile/static/a5694cb204f38cef612de44d0a04aa60/10479/advanced_machine_signal.png 115w,\n/mobile/static/a5694cb204f38cef612de44d0a04aa60/b7af2/advanced_machine_signal.png 230w","sizes":"(min-width: 230px) 230px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/mobile/static/a5694cb204f38cef612de44d0a04aa60/b423f/advanced_machine_signal.avif 58w,\n/mobile/static/a5694cb204f38cef612de44d0a04aa60/4b692/advanced_machine_signal.avif 115w,\n/mobile/static/a5694cb204f38cef612de44d0a04aa60/f6006/advanced_machine_signal.avif 230w","type":"image/avif","sizes":"(min-width: 230px) 230px, 100vw"},{"srcSet":"/mobile/static/a5694cb204f38cef612de44d0a04aa60/5aa2f/advanced_machine_signal.webp 58w,\n/mobile/static/a5694cb204f38cef612de44d0a04aa60/f8466/advanced_machine_signal.webp 115w,\n/mobile/static/a5694cb204f38cef612de44d0a04aa60/84992/advanced_machine_signal.webp 230w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min-width: 230px) 230px, 100vw"}]},"width":230,"height":230}}},"external":"https://www.credly.com/badges/4f1f016f-1c85-4792-86dc-a9d59d4a59ee/public_url","topics":["Supervised Machine Learning","Unsupervised Machine Learning","Linear Algebra","Hyperparameter Tuning"],"skills":["Apache Spark","Data Science","Digital Signal Processing","Internet Of Things","Machine Learning","scikit-learn"]},"html":"<p>This badge earner understands how machine learning works and can explain the difference between unsupervised and supervised machine learning. The earner is familiar with the usage of state-of-the-art machine learning frameworks and different feature engineering techniques like signal processing and dimension reduction. The individual can also apply their knowledge on different industry relevant tasks. Finally, they know how to scale the models on data parallel frameworks like Apache Spark.</p>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"date":"2020-07-04","title":"Basic Sentiment Analysis with TensorFlow","organizer":"Coursera Project Network","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/png;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/mobile/static/8ed32c55ff62a571e706c4a67a7ed6be/c4dc8/coursera.png","srcSet":"/mobile/static/8ed32c55ff62a571e706c4a67a7ed6be/dfe8d/coursera.png 58w,\n/mobile/static/8ed32c55ff62a571e706c4a67a7ed6be/c2b67/coursera.png 115w,\n/mobile/static/8ed32c55ff62a571e706c4a67a7ed6be/c4dc8/coursera.png 230w,\n/mobile/static/8ed32c55ff62a571e706c4a67a7ed6be/23cff/coursera.png 460w","sizes":"(min-width: 230px) 230px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/mobile/static/8ed32c55ff62a571e706c4a67a7ed6be/09917/coursera.avif 58w,\n/mobile/static/8ed32c55ff62a571e706c4a67a7ed6be/28e2f/coursera.avif 115w,\n/mobile/static/8ed32c55ff62a571e706c4a67a7ed6be/74e0c/coursera.avif 230w,\n/mobile/static/8ed32c55ff62a571e706c4a67a7ed6be/b2997/coursera.avif 460w","type":"image/avif","sizes":"(min-width: 230px) 230px, 100vw"},{"srcSet":"/mobile/static/8ed32c55ff62a571e706c4a67a7ed6be/9316a/coursera.webp 58w,\n/mobile/static/8ed32c55ff62a571e706c4a67a7ed6be/be6d2/coursera.webp 115w,\n/mobile/static/8ed32c55ff62a571e706c4a67a7ed6be/4aa35/coursera.webp 230w,\n/mobile/static/8ed32c55ff62a571e706c4a67a7ed6be/194dc/coursera.webp 460w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min-width: 230px) 230px, 100vw"}]},"width":230,"height":33}}},"external":"https://coursera.org/share/c33dab0e26acfd42e2d7655c6ea8f17f","topics":["Create, train, and evaluate a neural network in TensorFlow","Solve sentiment analysis and text classification problems with neural networks"],"skills":["Deep Learning","Artificial Neural Network","Machine Learning","Document Classification","Tensorflow"]},"html":""}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"date":"2020-06-26","title":"Fundamentals of Scalable Data Science","organizer":"IBM","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/png;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/mobile/static/a2940302e4fac381344466f0728a383f/5ba08/IBM.png","srcSet":"/mobile/static/a2940302e4fac381344466f0728a383f/65fcf/IBM.png 58w,\n/mobile/static/a2940302e4fac381344466f0728a383f/49b51/IBM.png 115w,\n/mobile/static/a2940302e4fac381344466f0728a383f/5ba08/IBM.png 230w,\n/mobile/static/a2940302e4fac381344466f0728a383f/ca5cd/IBM.png 460w","sizes":"(min-width: 230px) 230px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/mobile/static/a2940302e4fac381344466f0728a383f/5f851/IBM.avif 58w,\n/mobile/static/a2940302e4fac381344466f0728a383f/5fe6a/IBM.avif 115w,\n/mobile/static/a2940302e4fac381344466f0728a383f/60a70/IBM.avif 230w,\n/mobile/static/a2940302e4fac381344466f0728a383f/6a153/IBM.avif 460w","type":"image/avif","sizes":"(min-width: 230px) 230px, 100vw"},{"srcSet":"/mobile/static/a2940302e4fac381344466f0728a383f/cefe0/IBM.webp 58w,\n/mobile/static/a2940302e4fac381344466f0728a383f/60d86/IBM.webp 115w,\n/mobile/static/a2940302e4fac381344466f0728a383f/4a71c/IBM.webp 230w,\n/mobile/static/a2940302e4fac381344466f0728a383f/68917/IBM.webp 460w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min-width: 230px) 230px, 100vw"}]},"width":230,"height":92}}},"external":"https://coursera.org/share/bf0383f35c489f6375d16bb5daa32ddd","topics":["Describing how basic statistical measures are used to reveal  patterns within data","Recognizing data characteristics, patterns, trends deviations or inconsistencies, and potential outliers.","Identifying useful techniques for working with big data such as dimension reduction and feature selection methods","Improving efficiency of analysis of big-data with partitioning and parallel analysis","Visualizing the data in an number of 2D and 3D formats (Box Plot, Run Chart, Scatter Plot, Pareto Chart, and Multidimensional Scaling)"],"skills":["Statistics","Data Science","Internet Of Things","Apache Spark","pyspark"]},"html":""}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"date":"2020-06-12","title":"Deep Learning Specialization","organizer":"DeepLearning.AI","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/png;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/mobile/static/1e726d170d968e103587c4f1f30bc58f/b7af2/deeplearning.png","srcSet":"/mobile/static/1e726d170d968e103587c4f1f30bc58f/559e2/deeplearning.png 58w,\n/mobile/static/1e726d170d968e103587c4f1f30bc58f/10479/deeplearning.png 115w,\n/mobile/static/1e726d170d968e103587c4f1f30bc58f/b7af2/deeplearning.png 230w,\n/mobile/static/1e726d170d968e103587c4f1f30bc58f/24f3d/deeplearning.png 460w","sizes":"(min-width: 230px) 230px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/mobile/static/1e726d170d968e103587c4f1f30bc58f/b423f/deeplearning.avif 58w,\n/mobile/static/1e726d170d968e103587c4f1f30bc58f/4b692/deeplearning.avif 115w,\n/mobile/static/1e726d170d968e103587c4f1f30bc58f/f6006/deeplearning.avif 230w,\n/mobile/static/1e726d170d968e103587c4f1f30bc58f/16325/deeplearning.avif 460w","type":"image/avif","sizes":"(min-width: 230px) 230px, 100vw"},{"srcSet":"/mobile/static/1e726d170d968e103587c4f1f30bc58f/5aa2f/deeplearning.webp 58w,\n/mobile/static/1e726d170d968e103587c4f1f30bc58f/f8466/deeplearning.webp 115w,\n/mobile/static/